<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-462-506  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 462 506.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>ESD: The Electronic System Design Magazine  July 1989 v19 n7p39(5).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Keeping pace with color printers. (System integration)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bond, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Ink-jet and thermal transfer are the frontrunners in the race toperfect color printing, thanks to some newer techniques such asdye-diffusion thermal transfer and Cycolor, which producenear-photographic quality prints.andP;  Ink-jet technology has beenrefined and applications range from high-cost systems for prepressproofing to systems cheap enough to use with personal computers.andO;Thermal transfer gives good print quality for a slightly higherprice.andP;  This technique commonly uses a waxy ribbon with pigment inthe wax.andP;  A thermal head scans by the ribbon and applies heat toit, transferring the pigment-impregnated wax to the paper.andP;  Thiswill probably remain the preferred midrange choice, with laserprinters in the high-range, but anything could happen in thefast-moving field of color technology.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ColorNew TechniqueTechnologyInk-Jet PrintersThermal Printers.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographtable.andO;Caption:   (Address list of printer companies). (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>